				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: I need ideas... anyone?<a name="6260"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 13 03 9:36 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Singing steel will last you a very long time.  At level 63 I am still wearing a lot of the pieces.  Its hard to upgrade.  While it doesn't have stats on most of the pieces, the AC is very decent and most of the clickies are so useful that you will keep the gaunts, helm, and boots bagged after you are done with them.  I was originally going to upgrade to Thurg armor myself, but if you look at the stats on each, you normally lose AC and gain some relatively unimportant stats going from singing steel to resonant.  Therefore, when you are ready for Thurg armor, I recommend just getting the breastplate and the greaves if you can (need to get real lucky, my guild lives in Kael and I have never seen plate greaves or breastplate drop).  </span></td>
